<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,628,1266]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,952,978]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer, 2020" authorityName="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer" authorityYear="2020" box="[326,404,953,979]" genus="Hutton" pageId="15" pageNumber="65" rank="genus" status="nov. gen.">Hutton</taxonomicName>
submitted a description of this species to the Transactions and Proceedings of the 
<collectingCountry name="New Zealand" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
Institute issue for 1884, but publication was delayed until 
<date box="[925,1042,988,1015]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1885-05">May 1885</date>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hutton, F. W." box="[1059,1265,988,1015]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="54 - 58" refId="ref63959" refString="Hutton, F. W. (1885 c) The fresh water shells of New Zealand belonging to the family Limnaeidae. Transactions and Proceedings of the New Zealand Institute, 17, 54 - 58. [May]" type="journal article" year="1885">
<taxonomicName authority="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer, 2020" authorityName="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer" authorityYear="2020" box="[1059,1139,988,1014]" genus="Hutton" pageId="15" pageNumber="65" rank="genus" status="nov. gen.">Hutton</taxonomicName>
1885c: 54
</bibRefCitation>
), and was preempted by a brief description in an account of a meeting of the Philosophical Institute of 
<collectingRegion box="[1133,1259,1024,1050]" country="New Zealand" name="Canterbury" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Canterbury</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hutton, F. W." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="175" refId="ref63669" refString="Hutton, F. W. (1884 h) Meetings of Societies. Philosophical Institute of Canterbury. Christchurch, 5 th June 1884. The fresh water shells of New Zealand belonging to the family Limnaeidae. The New Zealand Journal of Science, 2 (4), 175. [July]" type="journal article" year="1884">
<taxonomicName authority="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer, 2020" authorityName="Brook &amp; Kennedy &amp; King &amp; Ridden &amp; Shaw &amp; Spencer" authorityYear="2020" box="[1273,1353,1024,1050]" genus="Hutton" pageId="15" pageNumber="65" rank="genus" status="nov. gen.">Hutton</taxonomicName>
1884h: 175
</bibRefCitation>
). Treated as a junior synonym of the Australian species 
<taxonomicName authority="Deshayes, 1831" authorityName="Deshayes" authorityYear="1831" box="[823,1191,1060,1086]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Limnaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lessoni">
<emphasis box="[823,1007,1060,1086]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Limnaea lessoni</emphasis>
Deshayes, 1831
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hubendick, B." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 223" refId="ref61697" refString="Hubendick, B. (1951) Recent Lymnaeidae; their variation, morphology, taxonomy, nomenclature and distribution. Kungl. Svenska Vetenskapsakademiens Handlingar, 3, 1 - 223." type="journal article" year="1951">Hubendick (1951: 180)</bibRefCitation>
, but according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Dell, R. K." box="[415,594,1096,1123]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="71 - 81" refId="ref60077" refString="Dell, R. K. (1956) The fresh-water Mollusca of New Zealand. Parts II and III. Part II-The species previously assigned to the genera Limnaea and Myxas. Transactions of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 84, 71 - 81." type="journal article" year="1956">Dell (1956: 76)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hutton" authorityName="Hutton, R. Avon" authorityYear="1884" box="[609,877,1097,1123]" class="Bivalvia" family="Unionidae" genus="Limnaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Unionida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="arguta">
<emphasis box="[609,790,1097,1122]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Limnaea arguta</emphasis>
Hutton
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="Pfeiffer, 1855" authorityName="Pfeiffer" authorityYear="1855" class="Gastropoda" family="Succineidae" genus="Succinea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis box="[1110,1336,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Succinea tomentosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pfeiffer, L." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="101 - 106" refId="ref66949" refString="Pfeiffer, L. (1855) Descriptions of a new genus and twenty-three new species of Pneumonopoma, from the collection of H. Cuming, Esq. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 23 (1), 101 - 106." type="journal article" year="1855">Pfeiffer, 1855</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. As noted in the preceding species entry, the latter taxon has a wide distribution in the North Island and South Island and is probably endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[537,691,1168,1195]" name="New Zealand" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,628,1266]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,434,1204,1230]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Current taxonomy.</emphasis>
A junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pfeiffer, 1855)" baseAuthorityName="Pfeiffer" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[713,1179,1204,1231]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Austropeplea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hygrophila" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis box="[713,990,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Austropeplea tomentosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pfeiffer, L." box="[1010,1172,1204,1231]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="101 - 106" refId="ref66949" refString="Pfeiffer, L. (1855) Descriptions of a new genus and twenty-three new species of Pneumonopoma, from the collection of H. Cuming, Esq. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 23 (1), 101 - 106." type="journal article" year="1855">Pfeiffer, 1855</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
— 
<bibRefCitation author="Dell, R. K." box="[1209,1385,1204,1231]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="71 - 81" refId="ref60077" refString="Dell, R. K. (1956) The fresh-water Mollusca of New Zealand. Parts II and III. Part II-The species previously assigned to the genera Limnaea and Myxas. Transactions of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 84, 71 - 81." type="journal article" year="1956">Dell (1956: 76</bibRefCitation>
—in 
<taxonomicName authority="Iredale, 1943" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1943" box="[151,428,1240,1266]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Simlimnea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hygrophila" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,269,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Simlimnea</emphasis>
Iredale, 1943
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
